<div type="definition">
<p>MUTUAL ADDRESSING EXCHANGED between those who MUTUALLY LISTEN.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current general word for engaging in familiar informal conversation is yǔ 語 (ant. mò 默 "say nothing").</p>
<p>2. Biàn 辯 refers sometimes to discussion or exchange of views typically among equals. See DISCUSS</p>
<p>3. Tán 談 refers to informal chatter or unrespectable intellectual dialogue.</p>
<p>4. Jiǎng 講 refers to the discussion of important subjects in the context of informal conversation, typically among equals. See EXPLAIN</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>會話 is the current modern word for a conversation.</p>
<p>對話 refers in a more formal way to a dialogue or exchange of views.</p>
<p>對白 refers specifically to dialogue in plays or operas.</p>
